    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1884-01-08T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1884-01-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="158"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d158">
                <head>No. 158.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Frelinghuysen</persName> to Mr.
                            <persName type="to">West</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1884-01-08">
                            <hi rend="italic">January</hi> 8, 1884</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: With further reference to the proposed
                    prolongation for an additional term of five years of the system of mixed
                    tribunals in Egypt, which was the subject of your note of December 13 last, I
                    have now the honor to acquaint you that this Government has duly received the
                    circular communication of the Egyptian Government alluded to, in which the
                    foregoing proposition was embodied, and has deemed it advisable to assent
                    thereto.</p>
                <p>Instructions have accordingly been dispatched that this conclusion be forthwith
                    signified to the Khedival Government.</p>
                <p>I have, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>FRED’K T. FRELINGHUYSEN.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
